  <Subject Subject_ID="300072984">
    <Parent_Relationships>
      <Preferred_Parent>
        <Parent_Subject_ID>300101707</Parent_Subject_ID>
        <Relationship_Type>Parent/Child</Relationship_Type>
        <Historic_Flag>Current</Historic_Flag>
        <Parent_String>perspective views by point of view [300101707], perspective views (visual works) [300034294], images by method of projection [300068504], images by method of representation [300033974], visual works by form of image [300191088], visual works by form [300191087], visual works (works) [300191086], Visual Works (hierarchy name) [300179869], Visual and Verbal Communication (hierarchy name) [300264552], Objects Facet [300264092]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refers to perspective drawings having a viewpoint well above normal eye level; for other nonphotographic depictions from a high viewpoint, where perspective is not used or is not emphasized, use "bird's-eye views." For photographs taken from high locations, use "aerial views" or "aerial photographs."</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Se refiere a dibujos en perspectiva que tienen el punto de vista sobre el nivel normal del ojo; para otras representaciones no fotográficas desde un punto de vista en altura, donde no es usada la perpectiva o no es enfatizada, use "vista a vuelo de pájaro". Para fotografías tomadas desde lugaress altos, use "vista aérea" o "fotografía aérea".</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Wordt gebruikt voor perspectieftekeningen vanuit een gezichtspunt flink boven normale ooghoogte; gebruik 'vogelvluchten (gezichten)' voor andere, niet gefotografeerde afbeeldingen vanuit hoog gezichtspunt, waarop geen perspectief wordt gebruikt of benadrukt. Gebruik 'luchtaanzichten' of 'luchtfoto's' voor foto's genomen vanaf een hoge plaats.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>以高於人類眼睛高度為視點的俯瞰透視圖。若是其他未運用或不強調透視法的高視角非照相類繪圖，則使用「鳥瞰圖」一詞。於從高地拍攝之照片，則使用「空視圖」或「航空攝影」等詞彙。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052784/TELDAP database (2009-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Perspektivische Zeichnung aus einer Sicht oberhalb der normalen Augenhöhe; für jede andere nicht-fotografische Darstellung von einem erhöhten Standpunkt, in der die perspektivische Ansicht nicht ausgeführt oder hervorgehoben ist, siehe ["Vogelschau (perspektivische Darstellung)"](300015529). Für eine Fotografie, aufgenommen von einem hoch gelegenen Ort, siehe ["Luftansicht"](300015527) oder ["Luftfotografie (visuelles Werk"](30012822).</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000122134/IfM Berlin</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refere-se aos desenhos em perspectiva que tem um ponto de vista bem acima do nível normal dos olhos. Para outras representações não fotográficas de um ponto de vista alto no qual a perspectiva não é usada ou enfatizada, use "vistas olhos de pássaro". Para fotografias feitas de locais altos, use "vistas aéreas" ou "fotografias aéreas".</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Portuguese</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000179/VP-intern</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000110648/Portuguese Translation Intern Project (2020-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
